obably what's creating those elongated, rigid flocks. I'm constrained to only modifying the shader and HTML though, not the core simulation or benchmark files. 6.8. With K=7 and the dense distribution of 20000 boids in a sphere of radius ~120, most should find enough neighbors within that range. The high aspect ratio of 20.39 likely stems from the large boundary sphere relative to the flock size, combined with gravity pulling everything downward and the grid-based neighbor search introducing subtle differences. Since dynamics is the real bottleneck, I should focus on increasing shape dynamics—either by boosting the perturbation kick strength from 2.5 to 3.5, or exploring other ways to add more variation to the movement.\n\nLet me check what the best baseline score actually was before these recent changes. Looking at the results, the quality experiments from experiment 18 onward got reverted, and the baseline was hitting around 1.0 before the grid change but now only reaches 0.57.\n\nSo I'm starting with a baseline of 0.5753 and launching into the optimization loop by testing experiment 269 with the perturbation kick strength increased from 2.5 to 3.5.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1182,"cache_read_input_tokens":59442,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1182},"output_tokens":13,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab277b0e-46f8-4888-a52e-c14b4b8bde67","uuid":"48bcc90c-f75a-40b0-a891-66e675d7e4c7"}
